                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/267</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-13T13:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 11, 4 p.m. The only French mill property in that section is the
                    Central Union owned by José Rousseau. It is not burned and was grinding
                    today.</p>
                <p>Colonel Betancourt, commanding considerable government forces at San Luis,
                    reports quiet in that district.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
